(1, '0', 0, 'Nhan', 'Nguyen', 'blackangelnt@gmail.com', '84909744117', 'test chuc nang repair service', '', 1, 0, 7, '', '2013-06-02 05:25:26', '2014-10-28 14:08:18'),
(2, '1075', 466, 'Anthony', 'Maccari', 'anthony@tonymac.ca', '4169091423', 'Zenmuse Z15', '330769108709', 1, 0, 4, 'We had a crash with the s800 and the gimbal was damaged. The gimbal requires some new parts (I labeled with green tape on the gimbal). The tilt also is not smooth and needs to be fixed. The gimbal does power up however a detailed test I was not able to do as my GPS was damaged during the crash.\r\n\r\nAlso side note - my order number 1075 was originally for the photo higher system but I upgraded to the Zenmuse and I am not sure why on your records this was never updated. I have all email correspondence on this if needed.', '2013-06-05 18:22:16', '2013-08-06 11:24:44'),
(3, '0', 0, 'Len', 'Metkowski', 'len.metkowski@gmail.com', '(215)-280-6009', 'S800', '320971734968', 1, 0, 4, 'Asses Repairs Needed, Provide Pricing, and call prior to beginning repairs. Phone number: (215-280-6009)\r\n\r\n\r\n[My s800 went down shortly after take off. I am not sure if it was a technical failure or due to the landing skids getting caught during takeoff.]', '2013-06-06 18:03:37', '2013-06-24 13:59:19'),
(4, '0', 600, 'mark', 'bailey', 'marcb61557@yahoo.com', '6096621710', 'DJI Phantom', '', 1, 0, 0, 'Crashed Phantom.  Replaced blades and removed NAZA.  Re-installed NAZA,  powers up but controls seem to be off.  as soon as i go above 50% power copter rolls over.  ', '2013-06-10 05:10:11', '2013-06-10 05:10:11'),
(5, '0', 600, 'mark', 'bailey', 'marcb61557@yahoo.com', '6096621710', 'Phantom', '', 1, 0, 7, 'Crashed', '2013-06-14 04:14:19', '2014-10-28 14:08:32'),
(6, '0', 0, 'juan', 'crane', 'jmcranef@yahoo.com', '01573165257488', 'zenmuse', '', 1, 0, 0, 'hard landing bumped the zenmuse and broke a couple of parts, also it will not calibrate correctly.', '2013-06-14 09:55:27', '2013-06-14 09:55:27'),
(7, '0', 0, 'Abdul', 'Houdi', 'aahoudi@yahoo.com', '419-290-4891', 'DJI S800 HEXACOPTER ', '', 1, 0, 0, 'The retractable landing gear is not working. We have tried your suggestions but they did not work either. Two days ago we came for another repair for the transmitter which did not work and the ground stations did not work either. We have flown the hexacopter yet, which we had purchased in April.  ', '2013-06-21 12:57:24', '2013-06-21 12:57:24'),
(8, '0', 0, 'MAURICIO', 'LOPEZ ESCOBAR', 'mjlemjle@gmail.com', '56999673751', 'DJI Phantom', '', 0, 0, 0, 'Hello, i have a problem, my RC broke the Switch GPS-ATTI, I need to repair, you can send me this part ? . You can see this files:\r\n\r\nhttp://imageshack.us/photo/my-images/706/eivw.jpg/\r\n\r\nhttp://imageshack.us/photo/my-images/841/34o5.jpg/\r\n\r\nhttp://imageshack.us/photo/my-images/4/khqf.jpg/\r\n\r\nI aks to send the part because i am from Chile (southamerica)', '2013-06-23 21:07:09', '2013-06-23 21:07:09'),
(9, '2147483647', 0, 'Jonathan', 'Kriegh', 'suddenincline@gmail.com', '6362620759', 'Zenmuse Z15', '', 1, 0, 0, 'Zenmuse does not start up correctly most of the time when powering up it will start and then just go limp (it does work fine for the first days use most of the time) after unplugging and re-powering several times it decides it will work for awhile and has just stopped in mid flight at times also when say stop it acts like it is not even powered up but the light on the bottom of the gimbal is red.\r\n\r\n\r\nJonathan ', '2013-06-25 13:24:39', '2013-06-25 13:24:39'),
(10, '1197', 815, 'Steven', 'Neville', 'realtimeaerialreview@gmail.com', '8138358182', 'S800 Retractable Gear', 'DJIS800RLGear', 1, 0, 0, 'The screws on both servos for the retract hinge broke and came out. The gear will not move when the servo moves.', '2013-06-27 08:39:43', '2013-06-27 08:39:43'),
(11, '0', 0, 'Greg', 'Lambert', 'greg@lambert.com', '651-335-9100', 'Phantom', '', 1, 0, 4, 'I had an inflight incident where the Phantom stopped responding to the transmitter and it crashed from about 30 feet in the air. While it was descending uncontrolably, it was rocking back and forth until it crashed. \r\n\r\nSince the crash, I have re-calibrated the IMU both basic and advanced, re-calibrated the transmitter, re-calibrated the compass both with a magnet and then the compass calibration mode (per the DJI video). \r\n\r\nThe Phantom can take off, but it will not hold a position in GPS mode and it will not return to a holding position if you rotate it or maneuver it right/left/foward/back.  It will move in the direction you give it stick to but it is hard to control it once you''ve started it in a direction.\r\n\r\nOne of the motors has more resistance when free-spining them. \r\n\r\nWhen running without props, I am unable to determine which motor has a higher pitched whine but it does occur when you use the sticks to give it direction without the props on.\r\n\r\nPlease take a look at this and troubleshoot to see if I need a motor replacement or what the issue may be.', '2013-07-01 11:18:07', '2013-07-10 10:45:17'),
(12, '2029', 800, 'William', 'Coughlin', 'wcough@gmail.com', '7163107753', 'DJI WKM', '01216430', 1, 0, 2, 'I purchased this package (DJI WKM + iOSD Mark II + LED BT + Data Link 2.4ghz + 50 Waypoint activation code)\r\nI want to receive the 50 waypoint activation code.\r\nand the single waypoint click/go activation.\r\nMy hardware ID for the controller is &quot;01216430&quot;', '2013-07-01 17:08:03', '2014-03-15 09:53:55'),
(13, '2184', 847, 'mike', 'marzo', 'herbie_53_guy@yahoo.com', '267-614-8051', 'DJI ZENMUSE H3-2D for GoPro cameras', 'ZenH32D', 1, 0, 4, 'Used 3 times, on fourth power up, the gimbal started to hum, then the gimbal died.  I still have power to the go pro, but the gimbal it self will no longer level', '2013-07-10 14:35:34', '2013-08-20 10:39:49'),
(14, '1578', 643, 'Mark', 'Fanslau', 'jmfanslau@gmail.com', '8566897121', 'DJI Phantom', '', 1, 0, 7, 'After installing Zenmuse H3-2D gimbal, I''m experiencing significant Jello-Effect, Vibration.\r\n\r\nSteps done to fix:\r\nIMU Calibration\r\nUpgraded to 3.14 Firmware\r\nBalanced Props\r\nAttempted use of different H3-2D Vibration Mounts\r\n\r\nStill experiencing effects, have noticed one engine is spinning slower than the other 3.', '2013-07-12 10:39:45', '2014-10-28 14:09:00'),
(15, '2185', 0, 'Ronald', 'Bulard', 'bulard@juellinc.com', '2129458218', 'Phantom Gimbal', 'Phantom Gimbal', 1, 0, 1, 'My gimbal started to squeel after the 3 rd flight.  It gets very hot and has now stopped working.', '2013-07-15 13:32:27', '2013-08-20 10:47:51'),
(16, '2147483647', 0, 'Jan', 'Jansen', 'jthorolfj@yahoo.com', '314 234 2459', 'Castle ICE2 HV 80 Brushless ESC', 'HES08001', 1, 0, 0, 'I have added connectors to the ESC. Tried it out on my pattern airplane motor. Unfortunately it does not work at all. There was no electric snap when plugging it on. According to Castle Creation FAQ there should be an audible snap to charge capacitors. I am tempted to send it in to Castle Creation for Warranty repair. I checked the voltage at the connector. It shoved full voltage. I had a friend hook it up to his PC with Castle programing. It also showed that the ESC does not power on correctly.\r\n\r\nThanks Jan', '2013-07-30 18:34:26', '2013-07-30 18:34:26'),
(17, '2147483647', 0, 'Steve', 'Carroll', 'Steve@previewfirst.com', '8587051600', ' DJI ZENMUSE H3-2D for GoPro cameras for Phantom', '', 1, 0, 4, 'Motor appears to have burned out on third test flight.  Barely used.  Powers on, but does not engage.  I understand per your email reply, that you may try to repair it. If you can do so successfully, and return it to me, no problem.  However, I have a feeling this is a faulty product that you would be better off returning to DGI.  I understand that it will take another week or so to get another one in stock. I''m perfectly okay with that. This whole process has taught me much patience.  Thanks', '2013-07-30 19:46:38', '2013-08-20 11:00:01'),
(18, '2147483647', 0, 'Tim', 'Cairns', 'timcairns@verizon.net', '7242388663', ' DJI ZENMUSE H3-2D', '?', 1, 0, 4, 'My DJI Zenmuse H3-2D has died shortly after installation.\r\n \r\n \r\nAfter the initial install the gimbal seemed to work.  Mirror test, first short flight,  all good.  Second flight, the gimbal came back limp and unresponsive.  Hasn’t worked since.\r\n \r\nAlso my GoPro LCD no longer works.  Fried it, I guess?   It has worked fine since the camera’s initial purchase  I can see what the camera is doing via the wrist remote, but not on the camera.\r\n \r\nWhile triple checking the setup and the gimbal not responding, the GoPro camera gets very warm after only a minute or so after start up?\r\n \r\nI’m certain I have everything installed properly.  All the firmware up to date.  (see attached images)\r\n \r\nI want the gimbal and would like an exchange.\r\n \r\nPurchased via ebay:\r\nitem number: 321146994908 \r\nusername: laurelmountain', '2013-07-31 08:19:21', '2013-08-16 09:00:39'),
(19, '2147483647', 970, 'Pavel', 'Savitskiy', 'mr.savitskiy@gmail.com', '+79166838768', 'DJI Phantom', '', 1, 0, 7, 'NAZA calibration error 25 after crash landing. Returning just NAZA controller for repair.', '2013-08-03 03:31:13', '2014-10-28 14:09:34'),
(20, '2425', 907, 'Harley', 'Finkle', 'Hfinkle@msn.com', '7608986500', 'DJI Spreading Wings S800 + DJI Wookong-M WK-M Autopilot Controller GPS Combo', 'DJI-S800-WKM', 1, 0, 4, 'two arm were defective... the elbow snap off while hovering at 2 feet on it second flight.no other damage to the arms, but the battery bent the top rails of the &quot;h&quot; frame, they cracked at the insert point. the helo realty did not hit hard, and the skids had thick foam on them which doesn''t even have a mark on them... the arms did not hit anything and look as new except the elbow is snapped off... I need the arms replaced and the four 12mm x 17cm rods of the top of the &quot;h&quot; frame... \r\n\r\nwas think about possible replacing them with solid carbon rods which will slightly increase the weight, but markedly increase the strength as the helo just had a hard landing about 1 to 1.5 g force, and the wt of the 6S battery caused it to bend and break at the insert point...\r\n\r\nI build camera ship as a professional... this is my first experience with DJI products... mostly ALIGN and our own systems...\r\n\r\nThank you for your help in advance...\r\n\r\nSincerely\r\n\r\nDr Harley Finkle \r\n\r\n760 898-6500', '2013-08-14 09:11:19', '2013-08-20 12:39:02'),
(22, '0', 0, 'Eric', 'Eddy', 'ee@stellaraerial.com', '3039412911', 'DJI Zenmuse Z-15', '', 1, 0, 4, 'The zenmuse z-15 has worked fine for months.  I flew it, snapped some pictures, landed it, swapped batteries, then when I plugged batteries back in, the zenmuse just started spinning wildly and would not complete its initialization sequence.  Now it just spins in a circle.  I have no idea what happened, it just won''t work now.  all the motors are functioning, it just seems as if the brains of the thing somehow stopped working.', '2013-08-19 12:59:50', '2014-02-21 15:12:22'),
(24, '0', 0, 'Greg ', 'Greenberg', 'Funnyeverywhere@gmail.com', '7705723731', 'T motors 2214', '', 2, 0, 4, 'After installing al motors, I found that 2 of the motors are defective. The props won''t unscrew clockwise or counter clockwise. Even with 2 wrenches. ', '2013-08-22 09:14:12', '2013-08-29 09:54:13'),
(25, '0', 0, 'JILL ', 'DELL', 'j106dell@comcast.net', '770-778-7633', 'DJI ', 'Phantom', 1, 0, 4, 'Our Phantom was up over 200 feet and struck by a bird. It hit our concrete driveway and two of the motors completely stopped working. In order to receive a claim on our Visa card for the insurance, we need a statement of repair costs (if repairable) by an authorized dealer. Can you help do this if we mail you the defective Phantom?', '2013-08-22 11:35:55', '2013-10-03 11:10:41'),
(26, '0', 0, 'Michael', 'Carter', 'kidwizdumb@gmail.com', '310 779 7647', 'Align T-REX 500 PRO DFC  Kit', '', 1, 0, 4, 'The kit you sent me went together great. However the canopy holes are drilled in a way that makes the shell look warped when fully mounted. The frame is very well aligned and nothing is askew. I even installed an old 500E Pro canopy on it and it fits perfectly.\r\n\r\nPlease send a replacement, or repair the canopy if possible.', '2013-08-27 11:15:01', '2013-08-30 12:11:40'),
(27, '2546', 978, 'Richard', 'Steinberger', 'richard@steinbergerphoto.com', '7203835238', 'DJI iosd mark II', '', 1, 0, 4, 'The iOSD doesn''t work completely. It transmits the flight data just fine, but does not transmit the video feed from the camera. The video feed works from camera when hooked up to video goggles or monitor, but is not being picked up by the iOSD... \r\n', '2013-08-28 10:11:51', '2013-09-04 12:46:24'),
