(29, '2362', 0, 'Richie', 'Kelch', 'Richiek@k2networks.com', '3109844646', 'S800+wookong', '', 1, 0, 4, 'Hello Richie,\r\n\r\nThank you for forwarding the message and telling us the problem. We''re sorry to hear about the crash. Let us clarify the first thing that you have in mind about the GPS. Like Robert said:\r\n\r\n&quot;For the GPS, does your GPS have V2 printed on the top of it?  If so it is the newest version.  The GPS with the black sides is actually a V1.  The V1 was upgraded to the V2 (1) with no black sides and NO V2 printed on it.  That one had the recall.  The replacement has the V2 printed on it.  They should have really called it a V3.&quot;\r\n\r\nThe recalled GPS is an issue in the past, last October-November 2012 only. We had help DJI recalling hundreds of GPS''s and sent back to them for bug fix. From Late November 2012 onward, there is no longer any more GPS that is subject to that bug, because they already have the new firmware from factory already. We''re on of the top DJI authorized distributors in the US, there is no point in selling a defective item in the first place, then doing the warranty later.\r\n\r\nTo see what is wrong with the system and do warranty service on whatever applicable, we would like you to return the products to us (ideally with your radio) so we can check at it for you. I have added a link below for you to fill out the form to receive you RMA number. Once you receive the RMA number, you can continue with shipping the product back to us.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nI am writing to you today to discuss my concerns with a Brand new S800 that I purchased 45 days ago.  Although I have been busy with work I finally found some time to walk through pretty much every DJI video on how to put the S800 together.  I have heard “Hi there I am Colin Guinn” more times then I care to repeat.  (-: the videos were very helpful and I finally got the S800 ready to fly last weekend.  I can tell you this is not my first Hex or my first DJI product.  I have had a F550 for the last year and it works perfectly today.  Anyhow, I got the S800 ready for its maiden flight, put it together, tested everything on the computer, put it out on the field, performed the GPS calibration, all systems go.  I put it into a 10-15 foot hover, all was well.  I flew it very slowly away, stopped, turned it around, flew it back to me, and still all was well.  Again I let it hover above for about 20 seconds and it held attitude and position nicely.  I flew it away from me again and stopped it about 30 yards away.  I began to see it drifting so I started to compensate but to my surprise it just kept on going until it flipped about 90 degrees and crashed into the ground.  I can honestly say that I was shocked.  At first I checked my radio but it had plenty of juice and the S1000 on it said the aircraft had plenty of juice.  I ran over and turned everything off, collected all the pieces, and returned home very perplexed.  I went online and started to research and after 2 hours I think I had figured out what the issue.  Even though I just purchased this brand new, I was given a GPS module that has been known to cause the aircraft to lose control in GPS mode and flip.  My GPS module is not the new version that has the black mark on the side of it, rather I have the older one that has been basically recalled.  First and foremost I am pissed off that I have spent countless hours putting this together and secondly that I would be given faulty equipment.  There were many used S800 out there but In my book there is nothing better than brand new and doing it yourself.  As a result of DJI giving out faulty equipment I am currently looking at a paperweight.  I have 2 full broken arms(meaning the arm, motor, prop are damaged), one antivibration bar is bent, plus a faulty GPS module.  I would like to know how I can get replacements for the 2 arms, props, motors, esc, antivibration, and a new GPS module.  How do I submit the paperwork necessary to get this started as I would like to actually get this aircraft up in the air.', '2013-09-03 14:06:40', '2013-11-22 21:11:25'),
(30, '2292', 889, 'Davide', 'Wyss', 'davide.wyss@skyworx.ch', '0041445602250', 'Boscam', 'FPV20BC', 1, 0, 4, 'As talked to Tony and Michelle over Skype, Boscam does not work with our DJI system. We would like a refund on our Paypal account. \r\nThank you very much for your help. We will ship you the Boscam back.  \r\n\r\nBest regards\r\nDavide', '2013-09-03 14:44:30', '2013-09-20 10:29:19'),
