(113, '5748', 0, 'jeff', 'kampner', 'kampner@optonline.net', '917-660-6247', 'dfi phantom 2 vision', '', 1, 0, 4, 'One of the rotor motors didn''t spin as freely as the others when I received the unit.  It flew fine the first time, but the second time it drifted into a bush and fell to the ground.  Prop continued to turn more slowly than the others and I was able to pull the rotor housing completely off the unit, exposing the coil.  I called in and was told that was not normal and should send it back.', '2014-03-05 16:33:40', '2014-06-05 10:52:54'),
(114, '0', 1676, 'Rafael', 'Pereyra', 'grafo.p@gmail.com', '976348353', 'Zenmuse H3-2D', '', 2, 0, 2, 'Hi, i purchased Zenmuse H2·3D for gopro, but i have 2 units broken.\r\n\r\nThe first one land into mud and shortc circuit the unit.\r\n\r\nThe second one had a hard landing and the Flex communicator broken at the bottom unit. (so i guess that replacing the flex can make the unit work again)\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCan you repair this units for me? Can provide me an stimate of reapirement costs?\r\n\r\nThanks a lot.\r\n\r\nRafael Pereyra D.', '2014-03-13 22:03:10', '2014-03-13 22:03:10'),
(115, '0', 2201, 'Cort', 'Glore', 'cortg@ymail.com', '678-772-4151', 'DJI Phantom 2 Vision', 'DJI-Phantom-II-Vision', 1, 0, 4, 'Updated firmware using the P2 software v1.08. After firmware update the unit flys very erratic. Will not stay in location when you release the sticks and the motors seem to jumper differently from each other causing is to shake.  Tried changes in the setting that Tech Support walked me thru with no improvements. I need to get it repaired or replaced.', '2014-03-17 17:00:35', '2014-04-11 10:41:37'),
(116, '6232', 1030, 'Mark', 'Johnson', 'mrcool148@hotmail.com', '660-385-1091', 'Phantom 2', '', 1, 0, 4, 'I just received my order, It came in a Pelican box, I removed the Phantom 2 charged up the batteries installed my Gopro Hero 3. I turned on the transmitter and the Phantom 2 the Zenmuse H3-2D gimbal stabilized, tried to use the tilt function with no response. Hooked up to the Assistant software moved the tilt lever, slider did not move.\r\nBut I found that if you held pressure to the tilt lever pivot screw the tilt function would work. I talked to \r\nJoseph Mitchell this morning and he thought that the pot had  got out of alignment during shipping and to send in the transmitter for possible repair or replacement. I have not even flew my new Phantom 2 yet.\r\n                Thank you, Mark Johnson', '2014-03-18 12:07:06', '2014-03-31 10:06:25'),
(117, '0', 0, 'John ', 'Baer', 'exnikon@aol.com', '609-947-7205', 'DJI 550', '', 1, 0, 4, 'Hi... I spoke to Doug earlier in the week about issues I''m having with my hex not holding its position when in the air - when it''s in the GPS mode it will &quot;wander&quot; and won''t stay in one steady position. I''m hoping you can figure out what''s causing problem.... Also, I''m having problems with the FPV - the signal only works with in about 100 feet and then it loses the signal and eventually goes to a blur screen - any thoughts on fixing that? Is it a cheap FPV package or is it something that can be fixed? Thanks - John Baer  609-947-7205 ', '2014-03-20 15:48:38', '2014-03-26 14:28:22'),
