(145, '0', 0, 'Bill', 'Frischling', 'bill@frischling.com', '703-623-1424', 'DJI Phantom Vision 2', '', 1, 0, 2, 'Hello...\r\n\r\nThanks so much for your help on the camera. I understand you couldn''t open it b/c the screw was stripped, but providing the case, the new power cable and the bottom case was above and beyond. I was able to fix the camera with the parts provided and it works fine.\r\n\r\nUnfortunately, that''s the only piece that works. Once I completed the install, the unit powered once (and the camera worked, thank you). However, there was no telemetry. It read every battery as &quot;not intelligent DJI battery&quot;, and the app streamed the video, but no GPS, camera control (pan/zoom) or other telemetry. (The camera works now, though :-) ). When connected to the computer, the GPS was not detected. I read online the video is WiFi and separate from the Naza, but the rest of the data routes through the Naza, which would lead me to believe that is the issue.\r\n\r\nI checked every connection 3 times, and the same issue was there, with the copter flashing red, yellow, green. I then updated the firmware to 3.0... big mistake. After that, the unit now just powers and beeps repeatedly. Nothing else.\r\n\r\nThe unit can now be opened and no screws are stripped. I''m hoping you can take a swing at repair. I''m also hoping it doesn''t involve sending to DJI, as they did provide warranty service, but quoted 4-6 weeks to turnaround, which is unacceptable to me. I''d rather pay you to repair in the next 7 days or so.\r\n\r\nI''d like to drop it off again tomorrow. Please let me know. Also, please let me know (I will call first) if I should close the casing... The screws are removed and the top plate can be removed... happy to leave it that way for your convenience.\r\n\r\nThank you.', '2014-04-30 19:47:50', '2014-04-30 19:47:50'),
