(158, '4564', 1442, 'JOSE', 'JIMENEZ', 'joseajimenez@me.com', '7328903920', 'DJI 2.4 GHZ Data Link', '', 1, 0, 4, 'I had not used the ipad ground station since I purchased it because I was planning on using it on my s800 evo and decided on waiting for the s1000. When I received my s1000 i mounted it on no problem. I rad alot of test on my s1000(gains, making sure everything was good to go before I mounted my zenmuse or started doing autonomous flights) In that time I misplaced the bluetooth to the receiver(?) so purchased a new one and received it on 5/21/2014. After setting everything up it shows a solid red light on the bluetooth and a red rx/tx light with a sometimes blinking sending green light. I have connected it to can bus port 2 on the dji a2 fc and also the pmu''s port with the cable in the box and still nothing changed. I even reset my a2, updated, and calibrated it still no go. I updated the firmware on the blutooth since it showed as available on the desktop data link application still no go. I also installed the desktop ground station control windows application (that i dont plan on using, i purchased an ipad just for the data link) and also didnt work which I didnt expect it to because of the lights that the components where showing which from the dji manual means there is a connection issue. sending overnight because I need a replacement really fast. I should also note that I am a member of RCGROUPS and I have read countless of threads on people having similar issues and its root cause because of being defective . please check it out at your earliest opportunity. \r\n\r\n\r\nReturn address should be,\r\nJose Jimenez\r\n2345 Peachwood Circle\r\n APT 5007\r\nAtlanta, GA 30345', '2014-05-22 09:55:06', '2014-05-28 12:17:45'),
