(175, '7931', 0, 'Clayton-Paul', 'Cormier', 'claytonpaul@maplesweet.com', '8027931515', 'Zenmuse H33D on Phantom 2', '', 1, 3, 7, 'gimble would not rotate up and down from start. contacted customer support this weekend and spoke with joseph or doug and he walked me through firmware adjustments but that failed to get the gimble working properly. Please replace or repair the faulty gimble, thank you.', '2014-06-10 13:56:53', '2014-10-28 14:03:42'),
(176, '0', 1225, 'Gary', 'Rushing', 'porchpicker@att.net', '901 457 9845', 'Phantom 2 Vision', '', 1, 0, 2, 'the camera on my vision has stopped working.  My phone does connect to the wifi but the camera icon on the dji app does not highlight so I can click on it. when I try to view the pictures stored on the micro sd card I get an error message that could not communicate with camera.', '2014-06-11 16:54:58', '2014-06-11 16:54:58'),
(177, '0', 0, 'Michael', 'Danielson', 'mike@eidecom.com', '612-385-1429', 'Zenmuse Z15-N NEX7', '', 1, 0, 4, 'This unit is malfunctioning and spins uncontrollably.\r\nPlease repair as soon as possible. \r\nThanks, \r\nMike', '2014-06-11 17:31:45', '2014-06-17 16:09:11'),
(178, '0', 0, 'Scott', 'Rodgers', 'scott@tierio.com', '703-801-4481', 'DJI Phantom 1', '', 1, 0, 4, 'Replace motor that cause the most vibration and the battery door', '2014-06-12 09:42:52', '2014-06-13 12:05:21'),
(179, '0', 0, 'Brian ', 'Kelly', 'brian@singlemaltmediatv.com', '703-282-1156', 'S800 Evo CW Complete Arm', '', 1, 0, 4, 'Motor quit while flying. Leaving motor + arm for inspection.\r\nThe motor quit while flying, but when I landed it did start up again. \r\nSo problem seems intermittent. Spoke with Jach on the Phone. ', '2014-06-12 11:41:22', '2014-06-30 20:41:41'),
(180, '0', 0, 'Mark ', 'Dumeyer', 'kram49@yahoo.com', '410-957-0875', 'Phantom 2 Vision +', '', 1, 0, 4, '-Broken Camera due to phantom crash.\r\n\r\nPlease carry out the following instructions:\r\n\r\n-Check functionality of copter\r\n-Add Phantom 2 prop guards\r\n-Contact if spare P2V+ parts arrive\r\n-Contact when main copter is complete', '2014-06-12 17:38:29', '2014-06-30 20:43:20'),
(181, '0', 0, 'Jeff', 'Morse', 'aerial.video.imagery@gmail.com', '2394644608', 'Phantom Vision Plus', '', 1, 0, 4, 'Phantom Vision Plus HD gimble turned on and started self check status.  Then the gimble started to shift up down, left and right erratically snapping the ribbon power supply to the HD camera.  There are several forums where other Phantom users have posted video and text on this same issue with the Vision plus gimble.  We were unable to hit the record button before the gimble lost control.  This is a faulty gimble and we would like to have the gimble replaced.\r\n\r\nThanks\r\nAerial Video &amp; Imagery ', '2014-06-14 07:14:12', '2014-10-03 12:40:05'),
(182, '0', 2822, 'David', 'Montminy', 'dpmontminy@gmail.com', '801-390-9828', 'DJI Phantom 2 Vision Plus', '', 1, 0, 6, 'Hello, \r\n\r\nI had an unfortunate accident with my new DJI Phantom 2 Vision +.  It did a RTH, but since the trees are so tall where I live it flew into one.  Overall the quadcopter appears to be OK with only damaged propellers, but the lens portion of the gimbal separated from the base and the ribbon cable connecting the two pieces together ripped. It is possible to get the gimbal repaired?  It looks like it might be an easy fix if they sell the ribbon cable.\r\n\r\nObviously, I can buy the completed gimbal and camera system from you, but I''m hoping for a less expensive option.  Does DJI offer a repair service for the camera system?  \r\n\r\nCould you please let me know what my options are?  Thank you, \r\n\r\nDavid \r\n801-390-9829\r\ndpmontminy@gmail.com\r\n', '2014-06-14 10:32:27', '2014-11-11 15:01:34'),
(183, '6745', 2051, 'MARK', 'DANDREA', 'mardoudan@gmail.com', '+506 8729 1622', 'A2 PMU', 'A2-PMU', 1, 0, 4, 'Reversed polarity.', '2014-06-14 10:52:43', '2014-07-22 09:43:27'),
(184, '0', 2453, 'Tom', 'Brown', 'brownth@cox.net', '703-405-7532', 'Phantom Vision+', '', 1, 0, 2, 'I had a hard landing (aka crash) with my Vision+.  The camera separated from the rear gimbal and broke the ribbon cable.  The camera body and lens look fine.  I want to see if you have the ability to repair the gimbal motor and ribbon cable.  \r\n\r\nPlease let me know what can be done.\r\n\r\nRegards,\r\n\r\nTom', '2014-06-14 22:31:55', '2014-06-14 22:31:55'),
(185, '0', 986, 'peter', 'ellin', 'peter@tinycars.biz', '631-782-8805', 'VISION +', '', 1, 0, 4, 'CUSTOMER PURCHASED THIS FROM UAS/ACES.....PURCHASED MOTOR AND ESC SPARE PARTS FOR REPAIR. PLEASE QUOTE FOR REPAIR AND BEFORE BEGINNING HAVE JAC/DOUG CALL ME FIRST. AFTER JOB IS COMPLETE IT WILL SHIP BACK TO ACES DEALS', '2014-06-16 08:45:14', '2014-07-24 12:19:21'),
(186, '0', 0, 'Sam', 'Gentry', 'stormybreeze@att.net', '6152384371', 'Phantom Vision Plus', '958265109874', 1, 0, 6, 'After starting up at 8 satellites, upon take off, flew up ten feet, hovered for a minute, flew aroumd for fove minutes, went up 100 feet, took two pictures went up 50 to 100 feet, went up another 100 feet, hovered, did 360 view ,, after hovering, crashed to ground, motor running. PLEASE CALL ME. Red and green lights solid entire time.', '2014-06-16 11:36:23', '2014-12-01 16:50:24'),
(187, '0', 0, 'Chris ', 'Riddick', 'chris@innovativefaith.org', '4349938187', 'DJI Phantom 2 Vision +', '', 1, 0, 4, 'We screwed the prop guard screws in without the guards on and believe that all 4 motors need to be replaced. ', '2014-06-16 16:25:27', '2014-06-27 15:41:24'),
(188, '0', 0, 'Pavel', 'Holyavkin', 'axegggl@gmail.com', '619-436-9034', 'DJI Phantom', '', 1, 0, 2, 'Hello, do you fix my quadrocopter Phantom 1 - DJI product?\r\nYou can see the broken part in this video:  http://instagram.com/p/pQWfFXyEeh/.\r\nHow much it will cost total and per hour tech time.\r\nWhere are you lokated?', '2014-06-17 20:36:44', '2014-06-17 20:36:44'),
(189, '0', 0, 'Michael', 'Esposito', 'mesposito@me.com', '7039328368', 'DJI S1000', '', 1, 0, 2, 'Spoke to Kevin this afternoon on the phone. Let him know that my wife will be dropping off my drone tomorrow (Wednesday) for repair at around 4:30pm. \r\n\r\nYesterday, during a shoot, the s1000 crashed. It happened immediately after takeoff. S1000 lifted off the ground about 4-5 feet and then drifted/tilted hard to the right and impacted the ground. No idea why this happened. Was not using the Lightbridge. The zenmuse GH3 gimbal separated from the s1000. I believe there is  damage to motors, arms, red locking bolts and props. Previously, I used a piece of lego to help add support to one of the arms holding the GH3 gimbal. \r\n\r\nI''d like to see if you can repair the s1000. Also, I will drop off my Futaba 14SG and DJI Lightbridge for installation and configuration (gains, mapping, etc.). I will include the charger for the Lightbridge ground unit, charging cable for lipo battery, etc.', '2014-06-17 23:52:25', '2014-06-17 23:52:25'),
(190, '7873', 0, 'robert', 'heilmeier', 'bobh@67live.com', '3017525386', 'dji', '', 1, 0, 2, 'check out camera  run test all  systems', '2014-06-19 14:06:13', '2014-06-19 14:06:13'),
(191, '0', 0, 'landon', 'irwin', 'landon.irwin@gmail.com', '8175380060', 'S1000', '', 1, 0, 2, 'Juan Deleon asked that I contact you to ask about how you are overcoming the issue of the analog out of the 5D GCU into the HDMI input on the lightbridge. Can you please provide your solution, we are wanting to see this before we pull the trigger on an S1000 from you guys.\r\n\r\nThanks,\r\nLandon', '2014-06-19 15:35:02', '2014-06-19 15:35:02'),
(192, '7870', 2668, 'Patrick', 'Johnson', 'kirilian@mediacombb.net', '256-476-1665', 'Zenmuse H3-3D Stand-alone', '', 1, 0, 4, 'During flight, the yaw axis motor will ''sleep'' every few seconds and then immediately wake back up.  This happens whether it is in forward flight (slow or fast) or hovering.  It only happens during flight, not on the bench.  I can provide video examples if necessary.\r\n\r\nThe gimbal is mounted on a F550 with Wookong-M flight control.  All firmware (Zenmuse and Wookong-M) has been updated to the very latest using DJI assistant software.', '2014-06-22 14:38:50', '2014-06-27 15:31:29'),
(193, '0', 0, 'Cristian', 'Simon', 'csimon@aerocam.cl', '5694344951', 'Zenmuse', 'Z15', 1, 0, 3, 'This is the second time that this Zenmuse repairs.\r\nIt was working perfectly, but now he began to have problems starting, not restart.\r\nNow turn very fast without control.', '2014-06-23 16:25:36', '2014-12-01 10:49:12'),
(194, '0', 0, 'Austin', 'Bowman', 'austinglasair@yahoo.com', '7573393102', 'DJI Phantom 2 Vision Plus', '', 1, 0, 2, ' My first issue:  My camera gimbal developed a 2-3 degree horizontal tilt.  Leaving all pictures tilted left side high and right side low.  After numerous re-calibration of all kinds, and ensuring the software was still up to date, I was unsuccessful in trying to correct the problem.  I consulted with the forums and it turns out I''m not the only one with this issue.\r\n\r\nFollowing the advice of many others who have had this problem on the forums, I flew the drone after calibration.  Supposedly this problem has been known to correct itself through exercising the gimbal and flying it for a period of time.  That''s when the second issue happened.\r\n\r\nIssue #2:  while exercising the phantom this morning for about 30 minutes I allowed too much drift to develop and the drone contacted the side of a child''s play bin.  The drone fell from exactly 1'' (I measured it).  Once ground contact was made, the same exact gimbal that was giving me problems that I described in issue #1 separated from the shaft and laid on the ground.  I have inspected for further damage and the drone flew perfectly and is free of damage save the detached camera from the gimbal. \r\n\r\nAt this point I''m frustrated with DJI''s lack of support.  More importantly, I''m more frustrated that I have no idea how to get this repaired.\r\n\r\n\r\nThank you in advance, and do please call me if required.  My number is 757.339.3102. I will be available through the day.  Please contact me if you would like pictures.  Thanks again!', '2014-06-24 09:42:11', '2014-08-18 09:30:21'),
(195, '5202', 0, 'Paul', 'Callahan', 'callahan_paul@hotmail.com', '3474897890', 'DJI Zenmuse 5D Gimbal', '', 1, 0, 6, 'Hi, my DJI Zenmuse 5D was damaged in small crash.  Please repair.  Also, I have included in shipment another H32D gimbal I would also like to get serviced.  I did not buy this gimbal from 1UAS but the gentleman on the phone told me I could send this in for repair too.  Thank you.\r\nPaul Callahan\r\n', '2014-06-24 11:09:27', '2015-01-06 14:34:19'),
(196, '0', 0, 'Brian', 'Kelly', 'brian@singlemaltmediatv.com', '703-298-2681', 'Zenmuse Z15', '', 1, 0, 6, 'Zenmuse unit has come apart.  Looks like it needs to have connections inside fixed or replaced.', '2014-06-27 14:41:54', '2014-12-12 14:25:16'),
