(204, '0', 0, 'David', 'Helmly', 'dhelmly@adobe.com', '4102671270', 'Vision Plus', '', 1, 0, 7, 'The DJI App on the iPhone only displays Black (no image) and it appears to be looking for a streamed signal for video. The camera controls are working fine on the iphone. You can take pictures and video and tilt up/up no problem. You just can’t see the streamed image coming from the camera to the iphone. It appears to be looking for the streamed signal and never finds it.\r\n\r\nWe’ve tried multiple iphones, resetting the Wifi and Binding and renaming the WiFi extender and no change. \r\n\r\nAll firmware is upto date.No new camera firmware that I can see.\r\n\r\nI did remove the top cover as requested to reseat the cables and no luck.\r\n\r\n\r\nThanks for the help,\r\n\r\nDave Helmly\r\n410-267-1270\r\n', '2014-07-07 15:25:56', '2014-10-28 14:02:36'),
(205, '0', 2754, 'Jordan ', 'Nelson', 'airnelson2007@yahoo.com', '828-850-0603', 'DJI H3-3D Gimbal', '', 1, 0, 7, 'My h3-3d gimbal mounted to my f550 has being having an issue with slight up and down movement while in use.  It''s had this problem since I received the unit but has gotten worse to the point where it''s very noticeable and occurs every 10-15 seconds.  You can''t really see the movement when it is sitting stationary but when watching the recorded video it''s very noticeable.  It''s a small twitch of a few degrees from the pitch motor.  \r\n\r\nI could not afford to wait for this to be looked at and have a new one sent so I purchased a new h3-3d that arrived today and that is why I''m sending this now.  Please let me know if you have any questions.\r\n\r\nThank you,\r\nJordan', '2014-07-08 11:38:28', '2014-10-28 13:28:51'),
(206, '0', 0, 'Joshua', 'Jennings', 'thelaw86.jj@gmail.com', '3869866493', 'DJI phantom 2', '', 1, 0, 4, 'Drone suffered in flight breakup and iosd and data link and gimbal were thrown from phantom .', '2014-07-08 13:45:52', '2014-07-30 14:19:04'),
(207, '0', 725, 'Jere', 'Snyder', 'jere@snypro.com', '919-846-5557', 'STO802', '', 1, 0, 2, 'I purchased this STO 802 Hexacopter from you last year and have flown it many times.  I recently installed a RC Timer brushless gimbal on it with a Martinez gimbal control and have flown it successfully.  However the gimbal had some bounce in it due to weak vibration dampers.  I added some extra ones that I bought from you and it helped however, one of the people working with me plugged in the power to the Martinez board wrong and fried it.  I replaced the board and flew it once successfully until the batteries needed to be changed.  When we changed batteries it started to fly erratically and we lost control of it and it crashed.  My guess is that the damage to the Martinez board also damaged the IMU or the Wookong.  My question is do yu have the capability to check all the systems and repair what needs to be fixed for me?  I will bring it to you and leave it if you can.  If not can you tell me who might be able to check these systems and help me?\r\n\r\nThanks\r\n\r\nJere Snyder', '2014-07-09 15:05:08', '2014-07-09 15:05:08'),
(208, '0', 986, 'peter', 'ellin', 'peter@tinycars.biz', '631-782-8805', 'VISION PLUS', '', 1, 0, 4, 'FULL REPORT OF WHAT HAPPENED TO THIS CRAFT IS ENCLOSED ON BOX....CUST CRASHED....AFTER HE REPAIRED PROPS AND REMOVED BROKEN CAMERA HE FLEW IT...SAYS IT FLIES PERFECT (SEE ATTACHED LETTER) BUT NOW IT HAS NO GPS.....PLEASE DIAGNOS, EMAIL OR CALL ME WITH RESULTS AND ESTIMATE TO REPAIR.\r\n\r\nPETER', '2014-07-10 14:01:26', '2014-07-28 14:53:22'),
