(224, '0', 0, 'Dave ', 'Helmly ', 'dhelmly@adobe.com', '4102671270', 'Phantom 2 Vision+', '', 1, 0, 4, 'The DJI App on the iPhone only displays Black(no image) and it appears to be looking for a streamed signal for video. The camera controls are working fine on the iphone. You can take pictures and video and tilt up/down without any problem. You just can''t see the streamed image coming from the camera to the iphone. It appears to be looking for the streamed signal and never finds it. \r\n\r\nWe''ve tried multiple iphones, resetting the Wifi, binding and renaming the Wifi extender and no change. \r\n\r\nAll firmware is up-to-date. No new camera firmware that I can see.\r\n\r\nI did remove the top cover as requested to reseat the cables and no luck. \r\n\r\nThanks for the help. ', '2014-07-30 13:10:22', '2014-08-12 09:28:56'),
