(227, '6164', 1442, 'Jose', 'Jimenez', 'joseajimenez@me.com', '7328903920', 'Jose Jimenez', 'DJIS1000A25D', 1, 0, 6, 'Gimbal was working perfectly fine until two days ago where a couple of things started happening. Notated below;\r\n\r\n1. The roll does not respond. In my video I can see the roll not balancing. If you connect to a s1000 or any capable multi rotor, hold up the frame of the multi rotor and do so roll movement and you will see it does not stabilize.\r\n\r\n2. The center location is no longer facing the nose of my s1000 instead faces on an s1000 in-between motors 3 and 4.\r\n\r\n3. It never made any weird noises ever before but not when it boots up its give or takes but it makes like a grinding noise, if you move the gimbal on its yaw axis either direction you might experience the noise. Its give or take. \r\n\r\nI have unmounted the gimbal to make sure nothing was caught inside and used a air cleaner to make sure no particles are stuck in the motors at all. Even retightened all the screws. I wasn''t sure if it was my eyes but then I compared footage and said yea something is wrong with the roll axis, and thats when I looked deeper and started seeing all the issues. This will be my second time sending in my zenmuse. Initially my first one when purchased was defected and wouldn''t work at all. This one has been great up until now. I am leaving for the dominican republic on 8/16 so if theres any chance of having it before then it would be great. If not please hold off on sending it back until I return on the 25th of August please.\r\n\r\n', '2014-08-07 00:02:23', '2014-10-15 10:58:09'),
