(447, '0', 0, 'Gary', 'Roberts', 'gary@hmmaz.com', '520-405-1407', 'Zenmuse H3-3D Gimbal', '', 1, 0, 6, 'After My Phantom 2 fell, the gimbal got bent, causing the footage from the gopro to be tilted, so that the horizon wasn''t flat but at an angle.  I bent it straight, and it worked fine until it fell again, and bent the gimbal in the other direction.  This time after bending it back into shape, the gimbal stopped working correctly.  Instead of pointing straight ahead, it now points about 45 degrees to the right or left, and there''s a noise coming from it that it wasn''t making before.', '2015-01-17 00:12:23', '2015-01-26 15:34:22'),
(448, '0', 0, 'Jay', 'Young', 'jayonthegorge@gmail.com', '3046405052', 'DJI Phantom 2', '', 1, 0, 3, 'She fell into a lake and was submerged to around 30 feet. I was unable to retrieve her for almost 24 hours. I dried her out for several weeks, but when I tried to boot her back up, she caught fire. Please diagnose and provide an estimate for repairs before doing anything else. ', '2015-01-19 13:01:04', '2015-01-26 11:53:09'),
(449, '14493', 0, 'Andrew', 'Uff', 'uffandrew05@yahoo.com', '609-706-7021', 'DJI Phantom Vision2 plus V3', 'Phan2-H3D', 1, 0, 3, 'I purchased this quad &quot;DJI Phantom 2 vision plus V3&quot; a couple of weeks ago. The hardware never came to connect the 7&quot; LCD screen that came with this package (I called already and told the problem) the customer service was very helpful. My younger brother has the DJI Phantom (without the GoPro) that I''ve been flying for awhile. That''s what made me make this purchase with you guys. I noticed that ''1 of 4'' of the rubber shocks was not connected right. Since I don''t have the screen brackets to connect the monitor, I only flew my quad once to see if the one rubber &quot;shocks&quot; that connect the gimbal to the Phantom was an issue. As soon as I took to the air approximately 20 feet off the ground, it took off right for a maple tree. I didn''t have any control, it just took off on me. It hit the branches then fell into the grass. Any questions please call me 609-706-7021. Thank you very much.', '2015-01-19 15:29:44', '2015-01-22 11:02:14'),
(450, '14377', 0, 'Justin', 'Davis', 'corekiteboarding@yahoo.com', '912-441-1412', 'Phantom 2 w/H3-3D', '', 1, 0, 3, 'I am having a hell of a time getting my Gimbal to work, in actuality, it has never worked.  When I originally unpacked the Phantom 2 that I bought as part of the Christmas special, Combo Pack with the video monitor and FPV set up, I powered up the Phantom and got no response from the Gimbal that was hanging underneath the Phantom.  \r\n\r\nI removed the Gimbal per Justins suggestion, so that I would not damage the unit while I learned to fly the Phantom.  After finally getting enough practice, I reinstalled the Gimbal and powered up the Phantom, but this time I had installed my GoPro camera, still nothing.  The Gimbal did not respond to anything.  I did notice that under the DJI Assistant software program, that the Gimbal limits board is greying out and I can not make any adjustments, the top bar of that board shows the number 52 and that is it.  Even when I clicked on FPV, nothing happened.  Still, no control of the Gimbal.\r\n\r\nFinally, I found the Anti-Interference board that had not been installed and temporarily connected it to the lead coming out of the bottom of the Phantom and then connected the lead from the Anti-Interference board to the appropriate connection on the Gimbal.  Powered up the Phantom and still nothing.  Believe me, I have CALIBRATED the controller and the Gimbal switch several times, but still nothing.  If the Assistant software program is to be believed, it would stand to reason that there is no communication between the Gimbal and the software, thereby indicating a failed Gimbal.  I say this because it there was communication, then the Gimbal Configuration under the Advanced setting would be possible.  \r\n\r\nI have no doubt that the Gimbal itself is at fault and want it replaced or repaired, I have already boxed it up an will return it with the Anti-Interference Board.  So I will need a Return Authorization to either UAS or to Drone Camps.  I would prefer to just send it back to UAS since UAS is responsible for putting this Combo Pack together.  We both know that it I send it to Justin, who is already aware of the problem, he will just turn around and mail it to you.\r\n', '2015-01-20 12:40:57', '2015-01-26 11:41:23'),
(451, '14085', 3924, 'Christopher', 'Costello', 'christophercostello@comcast.net', '215-350-0137', 'Thermal UAS Package', '', 1, 0, 3, 'The delivered package does not have the capability as described on your website.\r\n\r\n&quot;The mechanism can automatically compensate for your Phantom''s pitch movement. Maximum tilt angle is 35 degree below the horizon and can be adjusted by the controller during flight.&quot;\r\n\r\nIt is hard mounted to the body of the Phantom.  In addition the double sided tape does not hold the extra components mounted on the outside of the body.', '2015-01-20 13:13:22', '2015-01-22 10:56:53'),
(452, '0', 0, 'John', 'Pelura III', 'jpelura3@mac.com', '8569350487', 'Phantom 2 Vision Plus', '', 1, 0, 6, 'Camera is off angle upon powerup. ', '2015-01-20 16:11:49', '2015-01-26 15:07:43'),
(453, '0', 0, 'Tim', 'Hardy', 'tim@BAS-inc.net', '443-867-0049', 'Phantom 2 Vision+', '', 1, 0, 3, 'Install camera unit and wire harness\r\n\r\n\r\nDROPPED OFF:\r\n-Phantom 2 Vision+\r\n-P2V+ camera unit and wires\r\n\r\n\r\n*No batteries, props, radio included*', '2015-01-21 12:41:29', '2015-01-21 12:41:59'),
(454, '0', 3116, 'John', 'Anderson', 'johnanderson854@gmail.com', '7576510842', 'Phantom FC40', '', 1, 0, 1, 'I have an FC40 which transmit on 5.8ghz and it will not bind to the receiver. I replaced the receiver and still it would not bind. I checked my remote with the RC software and it woulds fine. I also tried a phantom vision 2 with the egg camera transmitter which works on 5.8ghz and it would not bind either. The LED on the outside of the aircraft is continually flashing yellow. In the battery bay the LED is flashing red and once pressing it turns yellow which means to turn on your transmitter for binding. Once the transmitter is on the light goes out in the battery bay but I''m still getting a continuously flashing yellow light on the outside LED. Any help would be kindly appreciated.\r\n\r\nR/\r\nJohn\r\n\r\n', '2015-01-22 10:58:22', '2015-01-22 10:58:22'),
(455, '0', 2111, 'Mark', 'Gaylor', 'info@nexgenhobby.com', '3015731149', 'DJI Phantom Vision 2+', '', 1, 0, 3, 'Customer crashed into tree and hit camera gimbal.  Gimbal erratic and will not initialize.\r\n\r\n', '2015-01-23 11:21:18', '2015-01-23 14:25:52'),
(456, '0', 0, 'Craig / James', 'Dry / Brann', 'southcoastclaims@gmail.com', '972-299-0809', 'Phantom2 vision', '', 1, 0, 3, 'We sent this craft in for service. We got it back and on its first flight it fly away,After looking for it for three months and posting a reward it was found, it a mile away .The craft was damaged because of the GPS not working correct.We feel that it is not our responsability to pay for damages caused by the Fly Away that accured after the GPS was serviced.', '2015-01-23 14:50:10', '2015-01-27 12:33:31'),
(457, '0', 0, 'Roger', 'Wolf', 'shop@dronesplus.com', '7022393409', 'Phantom 2 Vision +', '', 1, 0, 2, 'Gimbal control on controller does not work properly. The wheel will not lock the gimbal and makes it act erratically. Wifi is not working properly. Will allow phone to connect but says connection is broken. All updates have been done and also all calibrations. There seems to be physical or warranty issues that need to be addressed inside the unit.\r\n', '2015-01-27 14:22:47', '2015-01-27 14:25:25'),
(458, '14377', 2188, 'Justin', 'Davis', 'corekiteboarding@yahoo.com', '912-441-1412', 'Phantom 2 FPV Combo', 'DJI-Phantom2-ComboPack', 1, 0, 1, '1UAS,\r\n\r\nPINCHED WIRE INSIDE SHELL FROM BUILD PROCESS: NEEDS REPAIR.\r\n\r\nMark Harp was having problems with his Phantom tipping over mid flight. He says it just flopped over and crashed.\r\nHe tried to calibrate the IMU and no response. Mark discovered a pinched wire inside the Phantom 2. Looks like the techs\r\nclosed the lid of the Phantom on this wire possibly causing damage to the wire.\r\n\r\nWe will need to have this wire replaced. I have photos that I will forward to you.\r\nOverall the copter just needs to have this wire replaced, flight tested and shipped back.\r\n\r\nAll the best,\r\n\r\nJustin Davis\r\nDrone Camps RC\r\n912-441-1412', '2015-01-27 19:14:50', '2015-01-27 19:14:50'),
