(180, 116, 3, 1, 'Diagnosis of your Transmitter indicated that it was not able to tilt lever could not tilt the gimbal. \n\nTo repair the product, the back of the transmitter (TX) was opened. The position of the  yellow potentiometer that interfaces with the silver, metallic cross-head form the white tilt lever was compared to the position of the yellow potentiometer in a Phantom 2 TX with a Tilt lever that worked well in controlling the pitching of the  gimbal-camera assembly.\nAfter the comparison, we noticed that the metallic portion of the yellow potentiometer on the TX you returned was more bent than the one in the other TX. Therefore, the yellow potentiometer on your TX was re-positioned to match the position of the one in the other TX. This was done by re-positioning its bent metallic part . Afterwards, the tilt lever on your TX  was then tested to ensure that it was able to tilt an H3-2D gimbal with a Gopro Hero 3 camera on a Phantom 2. \n\nFurthermore, We upgraded the firmware on your TX to the the latest firmware (version 1.0.1.12) using the current (version 1.1)  Phantom 2 RC Assistant  Software. Although the tilt problem was fixed before the firmware update, we recommend downloading current  assistant software for the purpose firmware updates since firmware updates on a product enhances the performance of product.  It can be downloaded from the Phantom 2 or Phantom 2 Vision Product section of the DJI website. Here are also two links that will lead you directly to the download page:\n\nhttp://www.dji.com/product/phantom-2/download or http://www.dji.com/product/phantom-2-vision/download. Visit either two of these links occasionally in order to see if DJI has released a new assistant software or firmware. \n\nPlease feel free to contact us with any question(s), concern(s), or information you may have. Thanks\n\n\nUpdated by: Imo Jach', '2014-03-28 20:16:25'),
