(297, 162, 3, 1, 'Hello Hans,\n\nPlease keep in mind that you need to bind your Phantom with your Transmitter when you receive it. Because you did not ship the transmitter to us, so we had to bind it with another radio to fix your Phantom.\nThe button to bind the radio is on the bottom of the Phantom body. When you turn it on, there''s a red LED on that place. You press the LED/button, and you will see it blink yellow. Keep it for 5 second, then release it, turn on the radio. If the LED is gone, then you finish binding the transmitter with your receiver.\n\nAfter that, you remove the props, plug Phantom to computer, turn on software and check under RC tab: if you move the two sticks to lowest left position, would the RC bars move to the most left position? If yes, then you finish the job of binding, and can test the motors to see whether you can starts the motors or not. Usually it will just that, and you can fly again. But if you have any question, then let us know.\n\nThanks.\n\n\n\nThanks.\n\nUpdated by: Nguyen Tina', '2014-06-02 12:13:36'),
