(549, 222, 3, 1, 'Dear customer:\n\n1. After the first attempt to test flight your Phantom we observed that the Phantom drifted. We then change the compass and tested flight again - the Phantom did not drift a lot as before. It hovered on the acceptable range when it was on GPS mode.\n\n2. We changed the motors to Tiger motors and tested flight with it. Its performance now is good.\n\nThe Phantom is ready to go.\nThe new compass:  $19;\nRepair fee (installation of new motors and test flight): $100;\n\nTotal fee: $119;\nYou can pay the fee when you come and pick up the Phantom.\n\nHave a good day!\n\n\n\n\nUpdated by: Nguyen Tina', '2014-08-11 10:22:40'),
(550, 193, 3, 1, 'Repair ID at DJI China:\n140714MXS-7N5824\n\nShipped to China under this tracking number:\nCJ457303659US\n(https://tools.usps.com/go/TrackConfirmAction?qtc_tLabels1=CJ457303659US)\nReceived at China at July 22nd;\nStatus now: Waiting for repair fee report from DJI.\n\nUpdated by: Nguyen Tina', '2014-08-11 13:46:46'),
