(552, 227, 3, 1, 'Dear customer,\n\nWe checked the gimbal and saw that:\n\n1. Pan motor made strange sound. \n2. Gimbal did not level to designed position.\n\nThis gimbal is under 12 months warranty from DJI, but we will have to ship to DJI China to have them repair it. This process will take up to 2 months to get it back here with us. Would you want us to proceed it that way?\n\nThank you.\n\nUpdated by: Nguyen Tina', '2014-08-11 14:55:34'),
(553, 227, 3, 1, 'Gimbal GCU: 0250011049\nGimbal IMU:  0240011153\nUpdated by: Nguyen Tina', '2014-08-11 14:57:29'),
(554, 227, 3, 1, '&quot;\nHello,\n\nTwo months is unacceptable. There is clearly something defected with the item. Theres no choice to have it replaced right away? My first gimbal was replaced by you guys right away. My s1000 is my main rig that I just started running in tandem with my DJI RONIN. All of which I purchased from 1UAS. There has to be a better solution for this. Two months is way too long.\n\nJose&quot;\n\nHi Jose'',\n\nThe first one we can swap the new gimbal for you right away, as it was reported defective within 30 days of receiving the gimbal. This one you have been using for few months so it will go through standard warranty procedure of DJI China. \nUpdated by: Nguyen Tina', '2014-08-11 15:49:56'),
(555, 227, 3, 1, '&quot;\nHello,\nBased on the information I gathered on the website from the service flow it should be fixed be repaired under warranty by you guys. Also the warranty states if it cant be fixed it will be replaced. I hope you can understand two months is just unacceptable when I run a business of this gimbal specifically. I could understand 2-3 weeks. But 8 weeks? Thats just too long I will miss out on a lot of business. Is there any possible way you guys/girls could reach out to DJI for an exception? \n\nThank you!\n&quot;\n\nHi Jose,\n\nWe are sorry for the frustration you are having now. But we dealer cannot repair it  here. And no other dealer can do this. We don''t have parts to change for any gimbals. DJI has always refused our request of having parts of Zenmuse/gimbal to repair; So the product has to go to China to be checked by DJI China to fix first. If they cannot fix it, they will issue you a new one. So far, they has been able to fix all gimbal under warranty.\nUpdated by: Nguyen Tina', '2014-08-11 16:32:33'),
