(560, 231, 3, 1, 'The Repair work on the copter has been completed. Copter is waiting to be test flown. Copter will be test flown due to pick up.\n\nLabor hours/cost= 30 mins/ $25.00\nParts/Cost = None/$0.00\n\nWork Detail:\n\n-Updated firmware for central power board and main controller to version 1.0.1.32 and 3.06, respectively.\n\n-Learned that the cause of the loud beeping was due to one of the cables from the central power board not attached to the main controller. Cable         \n Cable was reconnected. \n\n-Properly reattached the H3-3D gimbal to allow the yaw motor to yaw or pan the gimbal farther. \nUpdated by: Imo Jach', '2014-08-12 13:30:45'),
