(671, 243, 3, 1, 'Detected the cause of the beeping problem your Phantom was experiencing. The problem is the battery. The battery that you were using has a dead cell. Therefore, the total number of cells on the battery is two instead of three. Since your system is NAZA-M Flight control system on your Phantom 2 was programmed to work with a 3 cell battery, the system detected an abnormal input voltage due to low voltage. Upon connecting the Phantom to to the NAZA-M Assistant software (version 2.20), the Voltage Low error message came up on the assistant software. Once  a battery with all 3 cells still active was used to power up the system, the beeping sound stopped and the low voltage error message was gone.\n\nSecondly, one of the motors needs to be replaced due to a bad bearing. \n\nTherefore, the total cost of repair are the following:\n\nPart/Cost\n-Phantom 1 Battery/$23.00 ---&gt;http://1uas.com/DJI-Phantom-Battery?search=Phantom%201%20battery\n-Phantom 1 motor (cw)/$24.00---&gt;http://1uas.com/DJI-Phantom-Motor-LEFT-Handed-Threads-M2M4?search=Phantom%201%20motor\n\nThere will also be a shipping cost associated with shipping back the system. \n\n\nUpdated by: Imo Jach', '2014-08-25 12:30:11'),
(672, 243, 3, 1, 'i need your permission to continue\nUpdated by: Imo Jach', '2014-08-25 12:38:23'),
(673, 241, 3, 1, 'Ok, then we will provide you the cable from FPV hub to zenmuse that you need. We will ship it back to you with the connection on, so you don''t need a picture. Just plug the iOSD on landing gear, Zenmuse cable under the bottom of Phantom2 to the last 8 pin port on the FPV. Connect gimbal with the camera Hero 3, turn on camera, and you should be just fine. The fact that you have iOSD on screen already confirm that the videolink is working. Because data from iOSD must be transmitted through Video link to show up on screen. Don''t wire the cable to connect videolink to main board, using FPV hub is much easier and safer.\nAlso, please pay for the shipping fee back to you: $20; as the product is not defective \nPlease send payment to our PayPal account: payment@intelligentuas.com and notify me when whe transaction is completed.\nThank you.\n\nUpdated by: Nguyen Tina', '2014-08-25 12:42:12'),
