(880, 287, 3, 1, 'By one new Radio 8J Helicopter:\nhttp://1uas.com/Futaba-8J-8-channel-2-4GHz-Computer-Radio-System-With-Receiver-R2008SB?search=Futaba%208J\nPRICE: \n$279.99; Futaba 8JH | Futaba 8J 8-channel 2.4GHz Computer Radio System with receiver R2008SB - Helicopter Version - Mode 2\nFree shipping.\n\nPlease send payment to our PayPal account: Payment@intelligentuas.com and let us know the transaction number so that we can ship out the product today.\n\nWe will help you program the radio once you get the radio home with you.\nSome note:\n1. Please check this manual to have correct connection from LB to Phantom (Page 24) and from LB to 8J (page 14): \nhttp://download.dji-innovations.com/downloads/lightbridge/en/Lightbridge_User_Manual_v1.0_en.pdf\n\n2. Turn on the 10J radio this way: hold the middle button on the radio (under + and - button) then turn on the radio. Menu: Power  -&gt; change to power off the system. This way Futaba will not transmit signal but receiving signal from LB;\n3. Hold the + button and get in to main menu:\n- Need to change Aux- Channel: SWE will control flight mode; Switch C will control IOC; VR will control the X1 channel (tilt function) and SWH to control force failsafe.\n- Need to change End point\n- Need to change P-Mix to get fail safe on Switch H;\nSkype ID: intelligentuas: Please call us on Phone before making Skype Video call.\n\n\n\n\n\nUpdated by: Nguyen Tina', '2014-09-29 15:45:23'),
