INSERT INTO `labpreorder_history` (`labpreorder_history_id`, `labpreorder_id`, `labpreorder_status_id`, `notify`, `comment`, `date_added`) VALUES
(1169, 350, 3, 1, 'Check-up on copter completed. Test flight was successful. IOC ( Course Lock and Home Lock) was tested.  It was tried at about 120 feet from home point. IOC testing was successful. The control sticks on the copter did what it was supposed to do. More than 6 satellites were maintained throughout the duration of the flight, as proven in the ability of IOC to work and with constant flashing green light from the two back arms. During IOC, the copter''s LED out was yellow and green, as stated in LED chart on page 24 of Naza-M V2 Quick Start Guide V 1.26 (see http://download.dji-innovations.com/downloads/nazam-v2/en/NAZA-M_Quick_Start_Guide_v1.26_en.pdf). I referenced this manual to you since you were flying in Naza Mode. In Naza mode, the LED output of the Phantom is the same as the LED out of the NAZA flight controller.  Gimbal still needs to be installed on it. We do not currently have any gimbal in stock. \n\nUpdated by: Imo Jach', '2014-10-31 13:00:03'),
(1170, 344, 2, 1, 'Copter has been tested. FPV functionality was enabled during the test.  FPV range test was 120 ft due to our location. No video signal was lost. Test flight was successful. Ready for pick up\n\nService Detail:\n-Installed two Phantom 2 Vision motors (1 CW and CCW) provided by the customer.\n-Upgrade the MC and Central Circuit Board firmware to 3.08 and 1.0.2.7, respectively.\n-Conducted test flight on system.\n\nPart/Cost\n-None/$0.00\n\nLabor/Cost:\n-1 hour/$50.00\nUpdated by: Imo Jach', '2014-10-31 13:16:29'),
(1171, 345, 3, 1, 'P2 vison plus was tested flight. Works fine. \nThe cost for the service is:\n$50 for labor fee;\n$15 for shipping fee (insurance and signature required to shipping address: 1165 w. highway 67, suite 323,alvarado,texas 76009)\n\nYou can pay us by sending PayPal payment to:\npayment@intelligentuas.com\nAnd notify us so that we can ship out the product right after you pay.\n\nThank you!\n\nUpdated by: Nguyen Tina', '2014-10-31 14:01:35'),
