(1175, 352, 1, 1, 'Hi Peter, \n\nIf you want to claim warranty on this one, please fill out the return form, not the repair form. Thank you.\n\nUpdated by: Nguyen Tina', '2014-10-31 15:38:48'),
(1176, 343, 2, 1, ' The helicopter is ready for pick up. Copter was test flown today. FPV functionality was enabled during the test flight. Flight test was successful. Please look out on your email for the video of the copter flying. I tried recording the what the aircraft is seeing. However, the SD cards I used could not store the video. \n\nService Detail:\n-Installed a new ESC on the copter\n-Installed 2 new propellers on the System\n-Upgraded main controller (MC) and central circuit board to 3.08 and 1.0.2.7, respectively. \n-Made sure solder joints are covered up properly.\n-Test flew the system. System flies very well. \n\nPart/Cost\n-Phantom 2 Vision ESC/$19.00\n-T Motor 9 x 3 Anti Gravity Propeller (2 Packs) (a set of 4)/$89.00\n-Phantom 2 Mounting Brackets/$75.00\n\nLabor/Cost\n- 2 hours/$100.00\n\nGrand Total\n-$283.00\n\n*Customer will bring in Data Link ground end module to make sure air end of data link connects with ground end in the Ground Station App.\n\nUpdated by: Imo Jach', '2014-10-31 16:59:18'),
(1177, 356, 5, 1, 'Not a drop off. Due to nature of the problem (customer complained of beeping sound upon power on), the phantom was fixed while customer was still at the facility.\nBeeping sound was due to 0% capacity left in the customer''s battery. After attempting to using a nearly fully charged battery, the beeping sound was eliminated.\n\nService Detail \n-Repositioned GPS module of the phantom by re-orienting the top cover of the Phantom 1 product.\n-Checked all wire connections\n-Checked battery life of customer''s battery and recommended purchasing a new one.\n-Upgraded Naza M firmware to 4.02.\n\nLabor/Cost\n-30 min/$25.00\n\nPart/Cost\n-None/$0.00\n\nTotal Cost\n-$25.00\nUpdated by: Imo Jach', '2014-10-31 21:32:08'),
